comparing code on terminal is hard, we want to use visual tools
we have some tools for this (KDiff3, p4Merge,WinMerge,...)
we wan to use or intellij

1. we should set intellij as default diff tool:
   git config --global diff.tool intellij         //we want to set it for all our repositories (global)
                                                  //we just set "name" for this default diff tool
                                                  //we set "intellij" as the name

2.then we should tell git how to launch intellij
  we have already add "idea" to PATH, so to say him open
  intellij for this tool name:
  git config --global difftool.intellij.cmd "idea --wait --diff $LOCAL $REMOTE"

Note: --diff means we want to open this editor
      for comparing.

Note: we use $LOCAL and $REMOTE as place holder
      for new and old files that we want to compare

3.we use "git config -e" to check our setting we configured,
  the place holders don't set for some reason!
  we add them manually to config file!

[difftool "intellij"]                                 [difftool "intellij"]
    cmd = "idea --wait --diff "	           cmd = "idea --wait --diff $LOCAL $REMOTE"

4.we can now use
  "git difftool" to see unstaged changes on intellij
  "git difftool --staged" to see staged changes on intellij



